   "source": [
    "## 6. Baseline 1 — Global Mean\n",
    "\n",
    "This baseline predicts the same value for every case: the average number of points observed in the training set.\n",
    "\n",
    "It is intentionally simple and provides a minimum standard that any useful model should beat."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 35,
   "id": "04a3fd8b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Baseline 1 - Train MAE: 5.612902540121161\n",
      "Baseline 1 - Test MAE: 5.552177835051548\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "global_mean = y_train.mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "baseline1_train_pred = np.full(len(y_train), global_mean)\n",
    "baseline1_test_pred = np.full(len(y_test), global_mean)\n",
    "\n",
    "baseline1_train_mae = mean_absolute_error(y_train, baseline1_train_pred)\n",
    "baseline1_test_mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, baseline1_test_pred)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Baseline 1 - Train MAE:\", baseline1_train_mae)\n",
    "print(\"Baseline 1 - Test MAE:\", baseline1_test_mae)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3d2fe137",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Baseline 2 — Grid Heuristic\n",
    "\n",
    "This domain baseline predicts points based on the historical average points associated with each starting grid position in the training data.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is stronger than the global mean because starting position is strongly related to race outcomes in Formula 1."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 29,
   "id": "f86308bb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Baseline 2 - Train MAE: 5.561859237494068\n",
      "Baseline 2 - Test MAE: 5.608548802912555\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "grid_avg_points = train_df.groupby(\"grid\")[\"points\"].mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "baseline2_train_pred = train_df[\"grid\"].map(grid_avg_points).fillna(global_mean)\n",
    "baseline2_test_pred = test_df[\"grid\"].map(grid_avg_points).fillna(global_mean)\n",
    "\n",
    "baseline2_train_mae = mean_absolute_error(y_train, baseline2_train_pred)\n",
    "baseline2_test_mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, baseline2_test_pred)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Baseline 2 - Train MAE:\", baseline2_train_mae)\n",
    "print(\"Baseline 2 - Test MAE:\", baseline2_test_mae)"
   ]
  },
